### What to Do

Replace the manual Unicode box-drawing code in DenialBox with rich_rust Panel. This is the PRIMARY rendering path for TTY terminals.

### Current Implementation (814 lines in denial.rs)

The existing code manually constructs ANSI escape sequences:
```rust
fn render_unicode(&self, theme: &Theme) -> String {
    let width = terminal_width().saturating_sub(4).max(40) as usize;
    let mut output = String::new();

    let color_code = ansi_color_code(self.severity_color(theme));

    // Top border with severity indicator
    let _ = writeln!(
        output,
        "\x1b[{}m╭{}╮\x1b[0m",
        &color_code,
        "─".repeat(width)
    );
    // ... 200+ more lines of manual formatting
}
```

### Target Implementation

```rust
#[cfg(feature = "rich-output")]
fn render_unicode(&self, theme: &Theme) -> String {
    use crate::output::{severity_to_box_style, severity_to_style, RichThemeExt};
    use rich_rust::prelude::*;

    // Build content using markup syntax
    let mut content = Text::new();

    // Header with icon and severity styling
    let severity_style = severity_to_style(self.severity.unwrap_or(Severity::High));
    content.push_line(format!("[{severity_style}]🛑 COMMAND BLOCKED[/]"));
    content.push_line("");

    // Command line with highlighting
    content.push_line(format!(
        "[dim]Command:[/]     [bold]{}[/]",
        truncate_command(&self.command, 60)
    ));

    // Reason
    content.push_line(format!("[dim]Reason:[/]      {}", self.reason));

    // Pack and pattern info
    if let Some(pack) = &self.pack {
        content.push_line(format!("[dim]Pack:[/]        [cyan]{}[/]", pack));
    }
    if let Some(pattern) = &self.pattern {
        content.push_line(format!("[dim]Pattern:[/]     [magenta]{}[/]", pattern));
    }

    // Explanation (if present)
    if let Some(explanation) = &self.explanation {
        content.push_line("");
        content.push_line(format!("[italic]{}[/]", explanation));
    }

    // Allow-once section
    if let Some(code) = &self.allow_once_code {
        content.push_line("");
        content.push_line("[dim]─────────────────────────────────────[/]");
        content.push_line(format!(
            "[yellow]To allow once:[/] [bold]dcg allow-once {}[/]",
            code
        ));
    }

    // Create Panel with severity-appropriate styling
    let box_style = severity_to_box_style(self.severity.unwrap_or(Severity::High));
    let border_style = theme.rich_severity_style(self.severity.unwrap_or(Severity::High));

    Panel::from_text(content.to_string())
        .title("[bold] DCG [/]")
        .box_style(box_style)
        .border_style(border_style)
        .padding((1, 2))
        .to_string()
}
```

### Key Changes

1. **No manual ANSI codes**: Use `[markup]` syntax
2. **No manual box drawing**: Panel handles borders
3. **Severity → BoxStyle**: Critical=double, High=heavy, Medium/Low=rounded
4. **Severity → border color**: Uses theme mapping
5. **Padding via Panel**: `.padding((1, 2))` instead of manual spaces

### Compatibility

Keep the old implementation behind feature flag:
```rust
pub fn render(&self, theme: &Theme) -> String {
    match theme.border_style {
        BorderStyle::Unicode => {
            #[cfg(feature = "rich-output")]
            return self.render_unicode_rich(theme);

            #[cfg(not(feature = "rich-output"))]
            return self.render_unicode_legacy(theme);
        }
        // ...
    }
}
```

### Testing

1. Visual comparison: old vs new output should look similar/better
2. Content parity: all fields rendered
3. Color correctness: severity colors match
4. Width handling: adapts to terminal width
