This phase enhances all CLI command output to use rich_rust features: Rules for section dividers, consistent Panel usage for info boxes, and improved formatting throughout.

### Why This Phase is P2 (Medium Priority)

1. **Depends on Phase 2 & 3**: Needs Panel and Table migrations complete
2. **User Experience**: Makes every CLI interaction feel premium
3. **Consistency**: Unifies output style across all commands

### Commands to Enhance

| Command | Current Output | Enhanced With |
|---------|---------------|---------------|
| `dcg doctor` | Plain text checks | Styled checklist with ✓/✗ icons |
| `dcg packs` | comfy-table | rich_rust Table with status icons |
| `dcg explain` | Plain text trace | rich_rust Tree visualization |
| `dcg stats` | comfy-table | rich_rust Table with colored metrics |
| `dcg test` | TestResultBox | Already migrated in Phase 2 |
| `dcg scan` | Progress + table | Enhanced ProgressBar + styled results |

### Technical Details

**doctor command:**
```rust
console.rule(Some("[bold] dcg doctor [/]"));
console.print("[green]✓[/] Configuration valid");
console.print("[red]✗[/] Hook not registered");
```

**packs command (pretty format):**
```rust
let table = Table::new()
    .title("[bold]Available Packs[/]")
    .with_column(Column::new("Pack ID").style(Style::new().cyan()))
    ...
```

**explain command:**
```rust
let tree = Tree::new(root_node);
console.print_renderable(&tree);
```

### Agent Safety

All JSON format output (`--format json`) bypasses rich_rust and outputs directly to stdout. Only `--format pretty` uses rich output (to stderr).

### Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `dcg doctor` shows styled check results
- [ ] `dcg packs` shows beautiful table with status icons
- [ ] `dcg explain` shows tree visualization
- [ ] `dcg stats` shows colored metrics
- [ ] All --format json outputs remain unchanged
